snippet: A shadowy Islamic extremist group said it had fired the two rockets in support of Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli jails.
abstract: Two rockets fired from Egyptian Sinai Peninsula strike southern Israeli resort town Eilat, causing no damage or injuries; attack, first such on that city in year, underscores continuing threat from militants operating across desert border.

byline.contributor: Fares Akram contributed reporting from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: A shadowy Islamic extremist group said it had fired the two rockets in support of Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli jails.

headline.seo: Rockets Fired From Egyptian Sinai Land in Israel
headline.main: Militants in Egyptian Sinai Fire Rockets Into Israel but Do No Damage
headline.print_headline: Militants in Egyptian Sinai Fire Rockets Into Israel but Do No Damage
